KISHAN SINGH V. STATE OF UTTAR PRADESH [1992] INSC 220 (2 November 1992)

 [LALIT MOHAN SHARMA, K. RAMASWAMY AND N. VENKATACHALA, JJ.] 
ACT:
 Code of Criminal Procedure 1973: Sections 374, 382, 383,384.
 Criminal appeal-Non-prosecution Power of Court to dismiss Held a criminal appeal cannot be dismissed for non- prosecution Appellate court should examine the petition of appeal and judgment under challenge and consider the merits of the case before dismissing the appeal summarily- Distinction between criminal and civil appeal discussed.
 Civil Procedure Code 1908: Order 47 Rule 11, 17 and 19.
 
